title: Phase Iia, Multicenter, Randomized, Third-party Unblinded, Adjuvant-controlled, Multiple Ascending Dose, Safety, Tolerability, And Immunogenicity Trial Of Acc-001 Withqs-21 Adjuvant In Japanese Subjects With Mild To Moderate Alzheimer's Disease.
description_brief: The purpose of this study is to assess the safety, tolerability, and immunogenicity of ACC-001, an investigational vaccine, in subjects with mild to moderate Alzheimer's disease in Japan.

outcomeMeasures.title: The Mean Changes in Alzheimer's Disease Assessment Scale-Cognitive Behavior (ADAS-Cog) Score From Baseline at Week 12, 26, 52, 78 and 104.
outcomeMeasures.description: The ADAS-Cog is a 12-item,objective measure of cognitive function, consisting of 1) Word Recall, 2) Naming Objects and Fingers, 3) Following Commands, 4) Constructional Praxis, 5) Ideational Praxis, 6) Orientation, 7) Word Recognition, 8) Recall of Test Instructions, 9) Spoken Language Ability, 10) Word-Finding Difficulty, 11) Comprehension of Spoken Language and 12) Concentration/Distractibility. For this study, the ADAS-Cog total score is derived by summing the individual scores from items 1 to 11. Total score ranges from 0 to 70 points, with higher scores indicating a greater degree of impairment.
outcomeMeasures.populationDescription: Efficacy analyses were performed on the modified intent-to-treat (mITT) population. The mITT population included all of the randomly assigned participants who took at least one dose of study medication, and had the baseline and at least one post baseline evaluation of the key efficacy variable (ADAS-Cog).

outcomeMeasures.title: The Mean Changes in Disability Assessment for Dementia (DAD) Score From Baseline at Week 12, 26, 52,78 and 104.
outcomeMeasures.description:
The DAD is administered through an interview with the caregiver and measures instrumental and basic activities of daily living.

A total score is obtained by adding the rating for each question and converting this total score out of 100. Higher scores represent less disability in ADL while lower scores indicate more dysfunction.

outcomeMeasures.title: The Mean Changes in Neuropsychological Test Battery (NTB) Score From Baseline at Week 12, 26, 52 and 78.
outcomeMeasures.description: The NTB is a composite of nine widely used neuropsychological tests that assess immediate and delayed recall of verbal and visual information, attention, verbal fluency and executive function. The cognitive tests included in the NTB are the Wechsler Memory Scale (WMS) Visual-Paired Associates (immediate and delayed), WMS-Verbal Paired Associates (immediate and delayed), Rey Auditory Verbal Learning Test (immediate and delayed), WMS-Digit Span, Controlled Word Association Test, and Category Fluency Test. The NTB z-score is used for analysis. The z-score for each component is calculated through the following formula: z = (y\_visit - y\_base)/SD\_base, where y\_visit is a value at a particular time point and y\_base is the average test score, and SD\_base is the SD based on all participants' observed baseline scores in the study.

certainAgreement.otherDetails: Pfizer has the right to review disclosures, requesting a delay of less than 60 days. Investigator will postpone single center publications until after disclosure of pooled data (all sites), less than 12 months from study completion/termination at all participating sites. Investigator may not disclose previously undisclosed confidential information other than study results.

explanation_target: Reason: The investigational product ACC-001 is described as a vaccine (immunotherapeutic) intended to elicit anti–amyloid-β antibodies by targeting the N‑terminal Aβ(1–7) peptide; that mechanism is aimed at reducing amyloid pathology (disease-modifying), which classifies it as a biologic targeting AD pathology. citeturn0search1turn0search4

Act: Key extracted details — ACC-001 is the investigational vaccine whose INN is vanutide cridificar; it is administered with the QS‑21 adjuvant in the reported Japanese mild-to-moderate AD studies; control arms included QS‑21 alone (adjuvant control) and PBS in some studies. citeturn0search2turn0search1

Reflect: Given ACC-001 is an active immunotherapy (vaccine) directed at amyloid‑β and designed to elicit anti‑Aβ antibodies (intended to alter disease pathology), the correct category is 'disease-targeted biologic'. No substantive ambiguity in the trial description suggests a different category (it is not a small molecule, not primarily a symptomatic cognitive enhancer, nor a neuropsychiatric symptom intervention). citeturn0search3turn0search0

Web search results (selected support): PubMed summary noting ACC‑001 (vanutide cridificar) as an anti‑Aβ therapeutic vaccine evaluated in Japanese subjects; reports safety, tolerability, and induced anti‑Aβ antibodies. citeturn0search1

Two Phase 2 multiple ascending‑dose studies paper describing ACC‑001 + QS‑21 as a potentially disease‑modifying vaccine aiming to reduce brain Aβ plaques; primary endpoints were safety and immunogenicity. citeturn0search4
Phase 2 amyloid imaging study summary (ACC‑001 with QS‑21) reporting immunogenicity and PET amyloid imaging endpoints. citeturn0search3
Long‑term extension data summarizing safety/tolerability and sustained anti‑Aβ antibody titers with ACC‑001 + QS‑21. citeturn0search0
explanation_agent: Reason: The investigational product ACC-001 (vanutide cridificar) is an active immunotherapeutic vaccine designed to elicit antibodies against the N‑terminal Aβ(1–7) peptide, with the intention of reducing brain amyloid‑β pathology — i.e., it directly targets amyloid‑β. citeturn0search4turn0search1

Act: Extracted details from the trial description and literature: ACC‑001 (vanutide cridificar) administered with QS‑21 adjuvant; primary goals were safety/tolerability and immunogenicity (anti‑Aβ IgG titers); exploratory endpoints included amyloid PET and biomarkers — all consistent with an anti‑amyloid vaccine approach. citeturn0search3turn0search5

Reflect: Classification check — the intervention is a disease‑targeted biologic whose mechanism is explicitly anti‑amyloid immunization, so the correct CADRO category is A) Amyloid beta. It is not multi‑target (no other pathway is the primary focus) nor a diagnostic/non‑therapeutic intervention. The PubMed phase 2 and extension reports confirm the vaccine’s anti‑Aβ design and clinical focus. citeturn0search0turn0search2
